    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - INSTALL - AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="8">
        <title>AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES</title>
        <para>When installing the countershaft assemblies into the countershaft bearings, keep the countershaft
            assemblies straight. Do not cock the countershafts.
        </para>
        <para>If, when the countershaft bearing cover is removed and you cannot see the snap ring groove, install the
            cover and drive the countershaft further until you can see the groove.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the countershaft assembly vertical on a clean, flat surface. If previously removed,
                use the proper driver and maul to install the countershaft bearing race (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017m0">Figure 220</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017m0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017m0" filename="../figg13/G13017m0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 220. Auxiliary Countershaft Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">In the countershaft rear bearing bore, use the proper driver and maul to install the
                countershaft bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017m1">Figure 221</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017m1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017m1" filename="../figg13/G13017m1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 221. Install Countershaft Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Temporarily install the rear bearing cover with two (2) bolts and no gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017m2">Figure 222</hotlnk>). The cover holds the bearing as the countershaft is
                driven into the bearing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017m2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017m2" filename="../figg13/G13017m2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 222. Install Rear Bearing Cover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use toolmaker's dye to mark the smaller LO range gear tooth that aligns with countershaft
                gear marked with an "O" (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017m3">Figure 223</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017m3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017m3" filename="../figg13/G13017m3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 223. Mark LO Range Gear Tooth</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the countershaft in the auxiliary housing. Mesh the countershaft marked tooth with
                either set of LO range gear marked teeth (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017m4">Figure 224</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017m4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017m4" filename="../figg13/G13017m4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 224. Mesh Countershaft Marked Tooth</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive the countershaft into the countershaft bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017m5">Figure 225</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017m5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017m5" filename="../figg13/G13017m5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 225. Countershaft Into Countershaft Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">From the auxiliary housing rear, remove the countershaft bearing cover and install the rear
                countershaft snap ring in the snap ring groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017m6">Figure 226</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017m6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017m6" filename="../figg13/G13017m6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 226. Rear Countershaft Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gasket on the countershaft bearing cover mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017m7">Figure 227</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017m7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017m7" filename="../figg13/G13017m7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 227. Apply Sealant, Tighten Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the countershaft bearing cover over the gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017m7">Figure 227</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017m7">Figure 227</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bolts, and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017m7">Figure 227</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat all steps for other countershaft installation.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
